Cox , Frontier Corp enter phone pact . Cox Communications Inc and Frontier Corp said Tuesday they had entered into a deal to offer long - distance telephone service to customers in select Cox markets beginning in the first quarter of 1997 . Cox said the five - year agreement calls for Cox to handle all marketing and sales to customers , while Frontier provides the long - distance network , telecommunications services , monthly billing and customer service . Cox said that through the deal with Frontier , its long - distance service will offer customers a choice of two simple , straightforward calling plans . 
